=Additional Aspects=

The simplistic view on elasticity presented in this section is useful in many ways. It should be noted however, that it is incomplete. The chapter <i>Continuum Mechanics</i> presents a theory of how 2D and 3D stress and strain fields interact.  Moreover, the material property <math>E</math>, may be influenced by several factors, including: temperature, aging and rate of deformation. Therefore, keep in mind that there is more to come on this subject later on in the book.



